Explosions occurred in the Podolsky district on the territory of one of the shopping centers and some houses. Rescuers, doctors and police are already there.

SES told CNN that the explosion happened near Retroville shopping mall.
        
 

Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveA Russian defence ministry spokesman has said a shopping mall in the capital Kyiv that was destroyed overnight killing at least eight people was being used to store rocket systems.
Russia used “precision-guided weaponry” to destroy a store of “multiple-launch rocket systems” and ammunition in a shopping centre in Kyiv, Igor Konashenkov told local media.
The attack took place late Sunday night, killing at least eight people , and setting a car lot ablaze
